PidTagPostalAddress.Description: Contains the mail user's postal address.

PidTagPostalCode.Description: Contains the postal code for the mail user's postal address.

PidTagPostOfficeBox.Description: Contains the number or identifier of the mail user's post office box.

PidTagPredecessorChangeList.Description: Contains a value that contains a serialized representation of a PredecessorChangeList structure.

PidTagPrimaryFaxNumber.Description: Contains the telephone number of the mail user's primary fax machine.

PidTagPrimarySendAccount.Description: Specifies the first server that a client is to use to send the email with.

PidTagPrimaryTelephoneNumber.Description: Contains the mail user's primary telephone number.

PidTagPriority.Description: Indicates the client's request for the priority with which the message is to be sent by the messaging system.

PidTagProcessed.Description: Indicates whether a client has already processed a received task communication.

PidTagProfession.Description: Contains the name of the mail user's line of business.

PidTagProhibitReceiveQuota.Description: Maximum size, in kilobytes, that a user is allowed to accumulate in their mailbox before no further email will be delivered to their mailbox.

PidTagProhibitSendQuota.Description: Maximum size, in kilobytes, that a user is allowed to accumulate in their mailbox before the user can no longer send any more email.

PidTagPurportedSenderDomain.Description: Contains the domain responsible for transmitting the current message.

PidTagRadioTelephoneNumber.Description: Contains the mail user's radio telephone number.

PidTagRead.Description: Indicates whether a message has been read.

PidTagReadReceiptAddressType.Description: Contains the address type of the end user to whom a read receipt is directed.

PidTagReadReceiptEmailAddress.Description: Contains the email address of the end user to whom a read receipt is directed.

PidTagReadReceiptName.Description: Contains the display name for the end user to whom a read receipt is directed.

PidTagReadReceiptRequested.Description: Specifies whether the email sender requests a read receipt from all recipients when this email message is read or opened.

PidTagReadReceiptSearchKey.Description: Contains an address book search key.

PidTagReadReceiptSmtpAddress.Description: Contains the SMTP email address of the user to whom a read receipt is directed.

PidTagReceiptTime.Description: Contains the sent time for a message disposition notification, as specified in [RFC3798].

PidTagReceivedByAddressType.Description: Contains the email message receiver's email address type.

PidTagReceivedByEmailAddress.Description: Contains the email message receiver's email address.

PidTagReceivedByEntryId.Description: Contains the address book EntryID of the mailbox receiving the Email object.

PidTagReceivedByName.Description: Contains the email message receiver's display name.

PidTagReceivedBySearchKey.Description: Identifies an address book search key that contains a binary-comparable key that is used to identify correlated objects for a search.

PidTagReceivedBySmtpAddress.Description: Contains the email address type for the end user represented by the receiving mailbox owner.

PidTagReceivedRepresentingEmailAddress.Description: Contains the email address for the end user represented by the receiving mailbox owner.

PidTagReceivedRepresentingEntryId.Description: Contains an address book EntryID that identifies the end user represented by the receiving mailbox owner.

PidTagReceivedRepresentingName.Description: Contains the display name for the end user represented by the receiving mailbox owner.

PidTagReceivedRepresentingSearchKey.Description: Identifies an address book search key that contains a binary-comparable key of the end user represented by the receiving mailbox owner.

PidTagReceivedRepresentingSmtpAddress.Description: Contains the SMTP email address of the user represented by the receiving mailbox owner.

PidTagRecipientDisplayName.Description: Specifies the display name of the recipient.

PidTagRecipientEntryId.Description: Identifies an Address Book object that specifies the recipient.

PidTagRecipientFlags.Description: Specifies a bit field that describes the recipient status.

PidTagRecipientOrder.Description: Specifies the location of the current recipient in the recipient table.

PidTagRecipientProposed.Description: Indicates that the attendee proposed a new date and/or time.

PidTagRecipientProposedEndTime.Description: Indicates the meeting end time requested by the attendee in a counter proposal.

PidTagRecipientProposedStartTime.Description: Indicates the meeting start time requested by the attendee in a counter proposal.

PidTagRecipientReassignmentProhibited.Description: Specifies whether adding additional or different recipients is prohibited for the email message when forwarding the email message.

PidTagRecipientTrackStatus.Description: Indicates the response status that is returned by the attendee.

PidTagRecipientTrackStatusTime.Description: Indicates the date and time at which the attendee responded.

PidTagRecipientType.Description: Represents the recipient type of a recipient on the message.

PidTagRecordKey.Description: Contains a unique binary-comparable identifier for a specific object.

PidTagReferredByName.Description: Contains the name of the mail user's referral.

PidTagRemindersOnlineEntryId.Description: Contains an EntryID for the Reminders folder.

PidTagRemoteMessageTransferAgent.Description: Contains the value of the Remote-MTA field for a delivery status notification, as specified in [RFC3464].

PidTagRenderingPosition.Description: Represents an offset, in rendered characters, to use when rendering an attachment within the main message text.

PidTagReplyRecipientEntries.Description: Identifies a FlatEntryList structure ([MS-OXCDATA] section 2.3.3) of address book EntryIDs for recipients that are to receive a reply.

PidTagReplyRecipientNames.Description: Contains a list of display names for recipients that are to receive a reply.

PidTagReplyRequested.Description: Indicates whether a reply is requested to a Message object.

PidTagReplyTemplateId.Description: Contains the value of the GUID that points to a Reply template.

PidTagReplyTime.Description: Specifies the time, in UTC, that the sender has designated for an associated work item to be due.

PidTagReportDisposition.Description: Contains a string indicating whether the original message was displayed to the user or deleted (report messages only).

PidTagReportDispositionMode.Description: Contains a description of the action that a client has performed on behalf of a user (report messages only).

PidTagReportEntryId.Description: Specifies an entry ID that identifies the application that generated a report message.

PidTagReportingMessageTransferAgent.Description: Contains the value of the Reporting-MTA field for a delivery status notification, as specified in [RFC3464].

PidTagReportName.Description: Contains the display name for the entity (usually a server agent) that generated the report message.

PidTagReportSearchKey.Description: Contains an address book search key representing the entity (usually a server agent) that generated the report message.

PidTagReportTag.Description: Contains the optional text for a report message.

PidTagReportTime.Description: Indicates the last time that the contact list that is controlled by the PidTagJunkIncludeContacts property (section 2.752) was updated.

PidTagResolveMethod.Description: Specifies how to resolve any conflicts with the message.

PidTagResponseRequested.Description: Indicates whether a response is requested to a Message object.

PidTagResponsibility.Description: Specifies whether another mail agent has ensured that the message will be delivered.

PidTagRetentionDate.Description: Specifies the date, in UTC, after which a Message object is expired by the server.

PidTagRetentionFlags.Description: Contains flags that specify the status or nature of an item's retention tag or archive tag.

PidTagRetentionPeriod.Description: Specifies the number of days that a Message object can remain unarchived.

PidTagRoamingDatatypes.Description: Contains a bitmask that indicates which stream properties exist on the message.

PidTagRoamingDictionary.Description: Contains a dictionary stream, as specified in [MS-OXOCFG] section 2.2.5.1.

PidTagRoamingXmlStream.Description: Contains an XML stream, as specified in [MS-OXOCFG] section 2.2.5.2.

PidTagRowid.Description: Contains a unique identifier for a recipient in a message's recipient table.

PidTagRowType.Description: Identifies the type of the row.

PidTagRtfCompressed.Description: Contains message body text in compressed RTF format.

PidTagRtfInSync.Description: Indicates whether the PidTagBody property (section 2.612) and the PidTagRtfCompressed property (section 2.935) contain the same text (ignoring formatting).

PidTagRuleActionNumber.Description: Contains the index of a rule action that failed.

PidTagRuleActions.Description: Contains the set of actions associated with the rule.

PidTagRuleActionType.Description: Contains the ActionType field ([MS-OXORULE] section 2.2.5.1) of a rule that failed.

PidTagRuleCondition.Description: Defines the conditions under which a rule action is to be executed.

PidTagRuleError.Description: Contains the error code that indicates the cause of an error encountered during the execution of the rule.

PidTagRuleFolderEntryId.Description: Contains the EntryID of the folder where the rule that triggered the generation of a DAM is stored.

PidTagRuleId.Description: Specifies a unique identifier that is generated by the messaging server for each rule when the rule is first created.

PidTagRuleIds.Description: Contains a buffer that is obtained by concatenating the PidTagRuleId property (section 2.943) values from all of the rules contributing actions that are contained in the PidTagClientActions property (section 2.628).

PidTagRuleLevel.Description: Contains 0x00000000. This property is not used.

PidTagRuleMessageLevel.Description: Contains 0x00000000. Set on the FAI message.

PidTagRuleMessageName.Description: Specifies the name of the rule. Set on the FAI message.

PidTagRuleMessageProvider.Description: Identifies the client application that owns the rule. Set on the FAI message.

PidTagRuleMessageProviderData.Description: Contains opaque data set by the client for the exclusive use of the client. Set on the FAI message.

PidTagRuleMessageSequence.Description: Contains a value used to determine the order in which rules are evaluated and executed. Set on the FAI message.

PidTagRuleMessageState.Description: Contains flags that specify the state of the rule. Set on the FAI message.

PidTagRuleMessageUserFlags.Description: Contains an opaque property that the client sets for the exclusive use of the client. Set on the FAI message.

PidTagRuleName.Description: Specifies the name of the rule.

PidTagRuleProvider.Description: A string identifying the client application that owns a rule.

PidTagRuleProviderData.Description: Contains opaque data set by the client for the exclusive use of the client.

PidTagRuleSequence.Description: Contains a value used to determine the order in which rules are evaluated and executed.

PidTagRuleState.Description: Contains flags that specify the state of the rule.

PidTagRuleUserFlags.Description: Contains an opaque property that the client sets for the exclusive use of the client.

PidTagRwRulesStream.Description: Contains additional rule data about the Rule FAI message.

PidTagScheduleInfoAppointmentTombstone.Description: Contains a list of tombstones, where each tombstone represents a Meeting object that has been declined.

PidTagScheduleInfoAutoAcceptAppointments.Description: Indicates whether a client or server is to automatically respond to all meeting requests for the attendee or resource.

PidTagScheduleInfoDelegateEntryIds.Description: Specifies the EntryIDs of the delegates.

PidTagScheduleInfoDelegateNames.Description: Specifies the names of the delegates.

PidTagScheduleInfoDelegateNamesW.Description: Specifies the names of the delegates in Unicode.

PidTagScheduleInfoDelegatorWantsCopy.Description: Indicates whether the delegator wants to receive copies of the meeting-related objects that are sent to the delegate.

PidTagScheduleInfoDelegatorWantsInfo.Description: Indicates whether the delegator wants to receive informational updates.

PidTagScheduleInfoDisallowOverlappingApp.Description: Indicates whether a client or server, when automatically responding to meeting requests, is to decline Meeting Request objects that overlap with previously scheduled events.

PidTagScheduleInfoDisallowRecurringAppts.Description: Indicates whether a client or server, when automatically responding to meeting requests, is to decline Meeting Request objects that represent a recurring series.

PidTagScheduleInfoDontMailDelegates.Description: Contains a value set to TRUE by the client, regardless of user input.

PidTagScheduleInfoFreeBusy.Description: This property is deprecated and is not to be used.

PidTagScheduleInfoFreeBusyAway.Description: Specifies the times for which the free/busy status is set a value of OOF.

PidTagScheduleInfoFreeBusyBusy.Description: Specifies the blocks of time for which the free/busy status is set to a value of busy.

PidTagScheduleInfoFreeBusyMerged.Description: Specifies the blocks for which free/busy data of type busy or OOF is present in the free/busy message.

PidTagScheduleInfoFreeBusyTentative.Description: Specifies the blocks of times for which the free/busy status is set to a value of tentative.

PidTagScheduleInfoMonthsAway.Description: Specifies the months for which free/busy data of type OOF is present in the free/busy message.

PidTagScheduleInfoMonthsBusy.Description: Specifies the months for which free/busy data of type busy is present in the free/busy message.

PidTagScheduleInfoMonthsMerged.Description: Specifies the months for which free/busy data of type busy or OOF is present in the free/busy message.

PidTagScheduleInfoMonthsTentative.Description: Specifies the months for which free/busy data of type tentative is present in the free/busy message.

PidTagScheduleInfoResourceType.Description: Set to 0x00000000 when sending and is ignored on receipt.

PidTagSchedulePlusFreeBusyEntryId.Description: Contains the EntryID of the folder named "SCHEDULE+ FREE BUSY" under the non-IPM subtree of the public folder message store.

PidTagScriptData.Description: Contains a series of instructions that can be executed to format an address and the data that is needed to execute those instructions.

PidTagSearchFolderDefinition.Description: Specifies the search criteria and search options.

PidTagSearchFolderEfpFlags.Description: Specifies flags that control how a folder is displayed.

PidTagSearchFolderExpiration.Description: Contains the time, in UTC, at which the search folder container will be stale and has to be updated or recreated.

PidTagSearchFolderId.Description: Contains a GUID that identifies the search folder.

PidTagSearchFolderLastUsed.Description: Contains the last time, in UTC, that the folder was accessed.

PidTagSearchFolderRecreateInfo.Description: This property is not to be used.

PidTagSearchFolderStorageType.Description: Contains flags that specify the binary large object (BLOB) data that appears in the PidTagSearchFolderDefinition (section 2.982) property.

PidTagSearchFolderTag.Description: Contains the value of the SearchFolderTag sub-property of the PidTagExtendedFolderFlags (section 2.685) property of the search folder container.

PidTagSearchFolderTemplateId.Description: Contains the ID of the template that is being used for the search.

PidTagSearchKey.Description: Contains a unique binary-comparable key that identifies an object for a search.

PidTagSelectable.Description: This property is not set and, if set, is ignored.

PidTagSenderAddressType.Description: Contains the email address type of the sending mailbox owner.

PidTagSenderEmailAddress.Description: Contains the email address of the sending mailbox owner.

PidTagSenderEntryId.Description: Identifies an address book EntryID that contains the address book EntryID of the sending mailbox owner.

PidTagSenderIdStatus.Description: Reports the results of a Sender-ID check.

PidTagSenderName.Description: Contains the display name of the sending mailbox owner.

PidTagSenderSearchKey.Description: Identifies an address book search key.

PidTagSenderSmtpAddress.Description: Contains the SMTP email address format of the email address of the sending mailbox owner.

PidTagSenderTelephoneNumber.Description: Contains the telephone number of the caller associated with a voice mail message.

PidTagSendInternetEncoding.Description: Contains a bitmask of message encoding preferences for email sent to an email-enabled entity that is represented by this Address Book object.

PidTagSendRichInfo.Description: Indicates whether the email-enabled entity represented by the Address Book object can receive all message content, including Rich Text Format (RTF) and other embedded objects.

PidTagSensitivity.Description: Indicates the sender's assessment of the sensitivity of the Message object.

PidTagSentMailSvrEID.Description: Contains an EntryID that represents the Sent Items folder for the message.

PidTagSentRepresentingEmailAddress.Description: Contains an email address for the end user who is represented by the sending mailbox owner.

PidTagSentRepresentingEntryId.Description: Contains the identifier of the end user who is represented by the sending mailbox owner.

PidTagSentRepresentingName.Description: Contains the display name for the end user who is represented by the sending mailbox owner.

PidTagSentRepresentingSearchKey.Description: Contains a binary-comparable key that represents the end user who is represented by the sending mailbox owner.

PidTagSentRepresentingSmtpAddress.Description: Contains the SMTP email address of the end user who is represented by the sending mailbox owner.

PidTagSerializedReplidGuidMap.Description: Contains a serialized list of REPLID and REPLGUID pairs which represent all or part of the REPLID / REPLGUID mapping of the associated Logon object.

PidTagSmtpAddress.Description: Contains the SMTP address of the Message object.

PidTagSourceKey.Description: Contains a value that contains an internal global identifier (GID) for this folder or message.

PidTagSpokenName.Description: Contains a recording of the mail user's name pronunciation.

PidTagSpouseName.Description: Contains the name of the mail user's spouse/partner.

PidTagStartDate.Description: Contains the value of the PidLidAppointmentStartWhole property (section 2.29).

PidTagStartDateEtc.Description: Contains the default retention period, and the start date from which the age of a Message object is calculated.

PidTagStateOrProvince.Description: Contains the name of the mail user's state or province.

PidTagStoreEntryId.Description: Contains the unique EntryID of the message store where an object resides.

PidTagStoreState.Description: Indicates whether a mailbox has any active Search folders.

PidTagStoreSupportMask.Description: Indicates whether string properties within the .msg file are Unicode-encoded.

PidTagStreetAddress.Description: Contains the mail user's street address.

PidTagSubfolders.Description: Specifies whether a folder has subfolders.

PidTagSubject.Description: Contains the subject of the email message.

PidTagSubjectPrefix.Description: Contains the prefix for the subject of the message.

PidTagSupplementaryInfo.Description: Contains supplementary information about a delivery status notification, as specified in [RFC3464].

PidTagSurname.Description: Contains the mail user's family name.

PidTagSwappedToDoData.Description: Contains a secondary storage location for flags when sender flags or sender reminders are supported.

PidTagSwappedToDoStore.Description: Contains the value of the PidTagStoreEntryId property (section 2.1022) of the message when the value of the PidTagSwappedToDoData property (section 2.1031) is set.

PidTagTargetEntryId.Description: Contains the message ID of a Message object being submitted for optimization ([MSOXOMSG] section 3.2.4.4).

PidTagTelecommunicationsDeviceForDeafTel.Description: Contains the mail user's telecommunication device for the deaf (TTY/TDD) telephone number.

PidTagTelexNumber.Description: Contains the mail user's telex number. This property is returned from an NSPI server as a PtypMultipleBinary. Otherwise, the data type is PtypString.

PidTagTemplateData.Description: Describes the controls used in the template that is used to retrieve address book information.

PidTagTemplateid.Description: Contains the value of the PidTagEntryId property (section 2.677), expressed as a Permanent Entry ID format.

PidTagTextAttachmentCharset.Description: Specifies the character set of an attachment received via MIME with the content-type of text.

PidTagThumbnailPhoto.Description: Contains the mail user's photo in .jpg format.

PidTagTitle.Description: Contains the mail user's job title.

PidTagTnefCorrelationKey.Description: Contains a value that correlates a Transport Neutral Encapsulation Format (TNEF) attachment with a message.

PidTagTransmittableDisplayName.Description: Contains an Address Book object's display name that is transmitted with the message.

PidTagTransportMessageHeaders.Description: Contains transport-specific message envelope information for email.

PidTagTrustSender.Description: Specifies whether the associated message was delivered through a trusted transport channel.

PidTagUserCertificate.Description: Contains an ASN.1 authentication certificate for a messaging user.

PidTagUserEntryId.Description: Address book EntryID of the user logged on to the public folders.

PidTagUserX509Certificate.Description: Contains a list of certificates for the mail user.

PidTagViewDescriptorStrings.Description: Contains view definitions in string format.

PidTagVoiceMessageAttachmentOrder.Description: Contains a list of file names for the audio file attachments that are to be played as part of a message.

PidTagVoiceMessageDuration.Description: Specifies the length of the attached audio message, in seconds.

PidTagVoiceMessageSenderName.Description: Contains the date of the mail user's wedding anniversary.

PidTagWlinkAddressBookEID.Description: Specifies the value of the PidTagEntryId property (section 2.677) of the user to whom the folder belongs.

PidTagWlinkAddressBookStoreEID.Description: Specifies the value of the PidTagStoreEntryId property (section 2.1022) of the current user (not the owner of the folder).

PidTagWlinkCalendarColor.Description: Specifies the background color of the calendar.

PidTagWlinkClientID.Description: Specifies the Client ID that allows the client to determine whether the shortcut was created on the current machine/user via an equality test.

PidTagWlinkEntryId.Description: Specifies the EntryID of the folder pointed to by the shortcut.

PidTagWlinkFlags.Description: Specifies conditions associated with the shortcut.

PidTagWlinkFolderType.Description: Specifies the type of folder pointed to by the shortcut.

PidTagWlinkGroupClsid.Description: Specifies the value of the PidTagWlinkGroupHeaderID property (section 2.1064) of the group header associated with the shortcut.

PidTagWlinkGroupHeaderID.Description: Specifies the ID of the navigation shortcut that groups other navigation shortcuts.

PidTagWlinkGroupName.Description: Specifies the value of the PidTagNormalizedSubject (section 2.806) of the group header associated with the shortcut.

PidTagWlinkOrdinal.Description: Specifies a variable-length binary property to be used to sort shortcuts lexicographically.

PidTagWlinkRecordKey.Description: Specifies the value of PidTagRecordKey property (section 2.904) of the folder pointed to by the shortcut.

PidTagWlinkROGroupType.Description: Specifies the type of group header.

PidTagWlinkSaveStamp.Description: Specifies an integer that allows a client to identify with a high probability whether the navigation shortcut was saved by the current client session.

PidTagWlinkSection.Description: Specifies the section where the shortcut will be grouped.

PidTagWlinkStoreEntryId.Description: Specifies the value of the PidTagStoreEntryId property (section 2.1022) of the folder pointed to by the shortcut.

PidTagWlinkType.Description: Specifies the type of navigation shortcut.
